description:
&lt;p&gt;Due to promotion within the team, an opportunity has arisen for an Administrative Support Assistant to join the busy Primary Care Office of NHS Wales Informatics Service (NWIS) based at Swansea.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NWIS are currently responsible for the implementation and support of IT initiatives in GP Practices, Prisons, Pharmacies, Opticians and Dental Practices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate would need to be IT literate, with a sound knowledge of Microsoft packages, possess excellent organisational skills, with the ability to identify priorities. Excellent written and oral communication skills are essential for this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role may require you to travel to various locations..&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews are likely to be arranged around 2 weeks after end date.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;**PLEASE NOTE: Due to Covid restrictions, interviews will be virtual and held over Microsoft Teams&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 19th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDavid WelsbyJob titlePrimary Care Team Leader (Swansea)Email addressdavid.welsby@wales.nhs.ukTelephone number029 2105 6815 (MS Teams)&lt;/p&gt;
